post_text:
Locker Assignments and Supply Drop Off - Grades 7-12

All students grades 7-12 are invited to come into the school to claim their locker and drop off their supplies. Students will be filtered in by grade as claiming lockers has always been done by seniority. Students will also be screened as they enter the building just like they will be come the first day of school. Please arrive within your scheduled time frame. If other arrangements need to be made please contact the school.

Seniors: 9:00-9:30

Juniors: 10:00-10:30

Sophomores: 11:00-11:30

Freshmen: 12:00-12:30

8th Grade: 1:00-1:30

7th Grade: 2:00-2:30

Technology Fee/Lunch Money

Students can bring technology fee payments today with them so we can start that process. You can also pay the technology fee online. You can also add lunch money to your accounts today if you would like.

Parents

We ask that only students enter the building today and we ask parents to remain in the car.

Winter Cheer

Mandatory Winter Cheer Uniform Sizing Meeting today at 9:15 in Stewartsville.

post_text: Thank you to everyone who responded to our Student Re-Entry Form! While the start of this school year is very different from others we are working hard to get everything ready for all of our Wildcats. Questions that were asked on the form will be addressed. We appreciate your patience! We are excited to welcome Wildcats back in the building. Please talk to your kids about washing their hands thoroughly and social distancing. More information in regards to the Virtual option will be available when we have our confirmation. Please be checking your emails as information is distributed. We wish all of our past, present, and future wildcats the best as we start the new school year.

post_text:
Our Osborn Wildcat Library proudly announces that we are going to be open again this summer!

Attached you will find a Reading Bingo card. When your child completes the reading task, just initial the box that task is in. When the Reading Bingo card is full, have your child return it to Mrs. Crabb at the library for a special prize!

Should there still be a stay-at-home order during any of these times, please feel free to email me any selections your child would like and I will check them out and put them in an envelope with your child’s name on it and leave it in the filing cabinet outside the main office doors.

Please note the following dates and times that our library will be open for your child(ren) to come and check out books during Summer 2020.

Osborn Library Summer Hours
Wednesday, June 10 530pm-7pm
Wednesday, June 24 530pm-7pm
Wednesday, July 8 530pm-7pm
Wednesday, July 22 530pm-7pm
Wednesday, Aug 5 530pm-7pm - book return

Thank you!

Sincerely,
Mrs. Crabb
Osborn R-0 School Library

Pop - Up Mobile Pantry Coming to Osborn, MO

What: Pop - Up Mobile Pantry

When: - Wednesday, June 10, 2020; Starting at 10:00 a.m. – Ending at 12:00 p.m. (While Supplies Last)

Where: Osborn School – 275 Clinton AVE - Osborn, MO (West Parking Lot)

Overview: Second Harvest Community Food Bank alongside volunteers will be distributing food through
a one-day mobile food drop in Osborn, MO starting at 10:00 a.m. Second Harvest recognizes the need
within this area and is taking action by bringing food to the food insecure individuals in each respective
community.
We are all in this TOGETHER!

This program is open to the general public. There are no income guides to utilize this program.

Due to COVID-19 our original Kindergarten Round-Up was postponed. We have rescheduled for Thursday, June 11 from 1:00-6:00 PM. Time slots will be available so please respond with the time that works best for you. April 10 at 5:47 PM ·

ATTENTION OSBORN SENIORS AND PARENTS!! The City has given us permission to light up the baseball field tonight!

Starting tonight April 10th, we will be joining schools around the country by turning on our baseball and football stadium lights on Friday nights at 8:20 pm, which is 20:20 military time, and leaving them lit for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020! We ask that you go outside your house to view them and share in this time with us as we honor the class of 2020! Please continue to follow CDC guidelines and stay safe!

Please tag or share this post so word can get out to all the Seniors!

ATTENTION OSBORN SENIORS AND PARENTS!! The City has given us permission to light up the baseball field tonight!

Starting tonight April 10th, we will be joining schools around the country by turning on our baseball and football stadium lights on Friday nights at 8:20 pm, which is 20:20 military time, and leaving them lit for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020! We ask that you go outside your house to view them and share in this time with us as we honor the class of 2020! Please continue to follow CDC guidelines and stay safe!

Please tag or share this post so word can get out to all the Seniors!

post_text: Osborn students swept the county spelling bee last night! Eighth grader Brookelin Clint won first. Fifth grader Soleah Arney won second. Eighth grader Elektra Thorpe won third. Fifth grader Benjamin Nichols won fourth. Brookelin and Soleah advance to regionals. #GoCatsGo

post_text:
Congratulations to Lady Wildcat, Kylee Grimes for a record breaking week! On Monday night versus Union Star she tied the record for most 3 pointers (7) in a single game.

On Tuesday against Nodaway Holt she broke the school record for Varsity Career 3 pointers. Her record currently stands at 143, but she isn’t finished yet!

Kylee Grimes
